after herself. As part of the assessment, a physical examination is undertaken and the following changes noted on her right hallux (Image). The woman says that her nail has looked like that for a long time and it does not bother her.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which of the following is the diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Onychomycosis","Onychocryptosis","Onychogryphosis","Onychauxis","Onychoschizia"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis is an example of \u003Cstrong\u003Eonychogryphosis. \u003C/strong\u003EOnychogryphosis is also known as ram\u0027s horn nail and is usually the result of neglect and failure keep nails trimmed - most often seen in the elderly, where there may be poor personal care. There is a yellow-brown thickening of the nail plate with associated gross hyperkeratosis. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOnychomycosis\u003C/strong\u003E is a fungal infection of the nail, which may become thickened and discoloured. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOnychauxis\u003C/strong\u003E is a thickening of the nail, without any deformity. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOnychoschizia\u003C/strong\u003E is splitting of the free-edged tip of the nail - this can be seen with frequent hand washing but can also be associated with normal ageing process. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe more familiar term for \u003Cstrong\u003Eonychocryptosis\u003C/strong\u003E is ingrown nail.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Onychogryphosis is a condition of neglect, usually in the elderly population."],"references":["Ko D, Lipner SR. Onychogryphosis: Case Report and Review of the Literature. Skin Appendage Disord. 2018;4:326\u2013330. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30410908/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"29061"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1497"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"medi